Social Media Sentiment Analysis
Description
This project aims to analyze social media data, specifically Twitter, to understand public sentiment towards specific topics, products, or events. By leveraging Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques, the project processes text data, extracts sentiment scores, and visualizes sentiment trends over time. This helps in deriving actionable insights for businesses, organizations, or researchers.

Features
Data collection using Twitter API with tweepy.
Text preprocessing (cleaning, tokenization, stopword removal, and lemmatization).
Sentiment analysis using libraries like TextBlob or Vader.
Visualizations of sentiment trends, sentiment distribution, and word clouds.
Clear and well-documented code with human-readable explanations.
Tech Stack
Programming Language: Python
Libraries:
tweepy (for Twitter data extraction)
pandas, numpy (for data manipulation and analysis)
nltk (for NLP preprocessing)
TextBlob or Vader (for sentiment analysis)
matplotlib, seaborn, wordcloud (for data visualization)
Tools: Jupyter Notebook, Twitter Developer API
